  "text": "These results suggest that immunoneutralization of endogenous CRH at the ME increases LH secretion probably mediated by LHRH release and the ME is probably one of the action site of CRH on LHRH secretion in addition to MPOA. In contrast to the present results, a previous report by [CITATION_1] has shown that the iv injection of CRH antiserum did not alter the decrease in the secretion of LH by suckling [CITATION_2] and concluded that the changes in LH secretion observed in lactating animals probably were not mediated by the effect of CRH at the level of LHRH release from nerve terminals in the ME [CITATION_3] . The reason why the differences between the present result and those of Walker et al. are not clear at the present time, but it may be due to the difference of CRH antiserum or physiological conditions in experimental animals. The other reports have shown that CRH inhibits the in vitro release of LHRH at the ME [CITATION_4] , and inhibit LH secretion mediated by opioid peptides at the level of the anterior pituitary [CITATION_5] . These reports support our results and suggest that the ME or the pituitary may be one of the action site of CRH on LHRH or LH secretion.",
